results.title: Starliner arrives safely back on Earth
results.summary: Boeing’s Starliner landed safely at 12:01 a.m. Eastern time on Saturday, Sept. 7 (1o:01 p.m. Mountain time, on Friday, Sept. 6).  After an extended stay at the International Space Station, Starliner’s reusable crew module touched down at its designated landing site, White Sands Space Harbor at the U.S. Army’s White Sands Missile Range in New […]

results.title: Starliner heads back to Earth
results.summary: Boeing’s Starliner spacecraft undocked from the International Space Station on Friday, Sept. 6, with separation confirmed at 6:04 p.m. Eastern time. The reusable crew module is expected to land at 12:01 a.m. Eastern time (10:01 p.m. Mountain time) Saturday at White Sands Space Harbor at the U.S. Army’s White Sands Missile Range in New Mexico. results.title: Boeing’s confidence remains high in Starliner’s return with crew
results.summary: Since Starliner’s Crew Flight Test (CFT) launch on June 5, Boeing and NASA have conducted extensive testing of its propulsion system in space and on the ground. results.title: Starliner Return to Earth Preps Underway
results.summary: Practiced, prepared, checked out, refilled, and inspected – the Starliner team is proceeding through checklists to be ready for return when a date is chosen. They spent Tuesday practicing for undocking during an integrated simulation with the International Space Station. results.title: Starliner Docked Hot Fire Testing Complete
results.summary: Spacecraft thrusters tested and helium system checked in second successful docked hot fire test. The Starliner team completed a docked hot fire test of the spacecraft’s Reaction Control System (RCS) thrusters Saturday afternoon, and monitored its helium system, providing additional data points for the Crew Flight Test’s return to Earth.
